title: Cross sections of He3 interaction with Nb-93 nuclei: experimental data and possibilities of their prediction

x4freetext: Cross sections of He3 interaction with Nb-93 nuclei:
experimental data and possibilities of their prediction

x4codes.hlp: Inst. Yadernyh Doslidzhen, N.A.N.Ukraini, Kyiv, Ukraine

x4codes.shortRef: Jour: Physics of Atomic Nuclei, Vol.59, p.2041 (1996)

x4freetext: English translation

flag.hlp: Reference to related data compiled in another entry

x4freetext: A detailed
description of the equipment used in this experiment to
irradiate the targets and to measure the gamma-spectra,
as well as the formulas for calculating the reaction
cross sections from the induced-activity values.
Pre-equilibrium emission and evaporation from
compound nuclei based on ALICE-85 code.

x4codes.hlp: Inst. Yadernyh Doslidzhen, N.A.N.Ukraini, Kyiv, Ukraine

x4freetext: Aluminum foils calibrated in thickness served to
reduce gradually the energy of incident 3He ions.

x4codes.shortRef: Jour: Physical Review, Part C, Nuclear Physics, Vol.25, p.770 (1982)

x4freetext: The stacks were disposed in Faraday`s cup
Two stacks have been used.
Three runs of measurements with different
time intervals were made.
Ultrapure germanium. The energy resolution
of this detector at Egamma = 1.3 MeV was 2.4 keV.

x4code.headerHelp: Error in value of quantity, defined under ERR-ANALYS

x4freetext: Errors in the cross sections comprise both
statistical and systematic uncertainties of the
experiment.
This uncertainty does not include:
Beam current uncertainty and
* decay data;
* systematic uncertainty of energies (1.0-1.5 MeV).
Needed corrections for secondary neutrons influence and
secondary electron yield from Faraday`s cup were
included.
Reaction lines are corrected
English translation of `YF` was added
SD:DECAY-DATA corrected in Subents 016,018,
032. Data were checked, title and author`s list
corrected according to PAN,59,2041,1996, except last
word in title: description -> prediction (compiler
believes that this is mistake in translation). Small
corrections in several Subents.  SAMPLE moved to
Subents 002-036. ERR-T -> DATA-ERR in Subents 002-036.
MONITOR, REL-REF were added.  ANALYSIS (AREA) deleted
(not relevant).
Independent
Stacks of Al, Co and chemically pure Nb were used;
the foils were collect in stack,the thicknesses
of Nb was 30-23 mg/cm**2, of Al 52-12 mg/cm**2, of
Co 27-23 mg/cm**2. Irradiation time for activities
was 15. hr, beam flux=1.44 x 10**15 He-3 ions.
Cobalt targets in the long-lived assembly were
irradiated to measure the cross sections for reactions
on Co-59 nuclei.
